# continuwuity (Matrix homeserver) config. Env prefix is CONTINUWUITY_ (this
# fork renamed the CONDUWUIT_ prefix used by the archived upstream conduwuit).
#
# Registration is CLOSED. Both accounts (@josh admin + the baibot "hermes" bot
# user) were created 2026-07-21, so the endpoint is shut. NOTE: continuwuity
# ignores the configured token for the FIRST account and instead prints a
# one-time bootstrap token to its logs; that first account becomes admin. To
# add another account later: set ALLOW_REGISTRATION=true, redeploy, register
# with CONTINUWUITY_REGISTRATION_TOKEN, then set it back to false.
#
# server_name uses the .lab. subdomain (internal-only, via npm-internal - see
# README.md in this directory) rather than the bare domain used by
# Traefik-fronted services. server_name is baked into every Matrix user ID
# and federation event at registration time and cannot be changed later
# without a full homeserver migration, so this must be correct before first
# start - nothing is deployed yet, so getting it right now is free.
CONTINUWUITY_SERVER_NAME=matrix.lab.{{ secret_domain }}
CONTINUWUITY_ADDRESS=0.0.0.0
CONTINUWUITY_PORT=8008
CONTINUWUITY_DATABASE_PATH=/var/lib/continuwuity
CONTINUWUITY_ALLOW_REGISTRATION=false
CONTINUWUITY_REGISTRATION_TOKEN={{ secret_continuwuity_registration_token }}
CONTINUWUITY_ALLOW_FEDERATION=false
# (well_known client URL intentionally unset: continuwuity derives it from
# server_name, and the old flat CONTINUWUITY_WELL_KNOWN_CLIENT key is deprecated
# — it was logged as "unknown, ignoring" on this version.)
